      "comment": "BINNAWAY PEARL (8) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a neck win at Angle Park in a handy 19.52. Draws out wide but goes well over this trip. Has a strong record from this draw, notching six wins and three minor placings from nine starts. Well placed and will be tough to beat. DANYO'S ALBIE (1) made it two minor placings on the trot when beaten third (17.21) in a Grade 5 at Murray Bridge last time out. Can find the frame this time. YARRAMUNDI OPAL (4) goes very well this course and distance starting 46 times for 20 wins and 18 minors. Hit the frame latest (17.14) when third at this track in a OPEN. Among the main chances. TECHNO KELLI (2) is worth including after a top-three finish in a tight contest most recently.",
